---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
// Also, you can import multiple files with Astro.glob
const posts = await Astro.glob('../pages/commands/*.md');
console.log(posts.map(p => ({ text: p.frontmatter.title, link: p.url })));
const section = "commands"
---

<MainLayout {section}>

	<h1>
		Commands
	</h1>

	You can use the console to add, tweak, and replace elements of your game, including your mini-map, your HUD, and
	more. Knowledge is key in CSGO so you should check out our guide to find out everything you can customize ingame.


	<h2>
		Command Pages
	</h2>
	<ul>
		{posts.map(post => <li>{post.frontmatter.title}</li>)}
	</ul>
</MainLayout>

